inn1.comm: Hopes is away, loosener really, overpitched on the off stump, presents the full face and drives it back past the bowler to beat mid-on to the boundary, sign of things to come?
and again, full on the off, bisects the gap between cover and point for a couple more, good stride forward, got to the pitch and played it confidently
held it back a touch, short of a good length on the off, defended into the leg side
bowled at 131.5 kmph, drawing him forward, tempting line outside off, pushed to cover
much closer to the stumps, bowled at 128.5 kmph, defended to cover, no movement so far, not exactly a fast bowler's pitch this
misfield at square leg, flicked away from outside off, fumbles and they steal a single, nice, assured start by Hopes
got it to move it away a touch, short on the off at around 122 kmph, guided to third man
nicely done, a touch fuller and shaping away, Haddin leaves it alone
poor ball, first impressions can be wrong, started off nicely but bowled a rubbish delivery outside leg stump, Haddin had no trouble clipping it to the fine-leg boundary
ominous signs these, full on the off, gets to the pitch and eases it through the covers, opened the face slightly and squeezed it through the gap
brought it back in this time, but he handled it well, got nicely behind it and pushed it back to the  bowler
cramping him on the off stump, the inswinger again bowled at 128 kmph, defended solidly back to Tanvir
good length on the off stump, plants his foot forward and blocks
came in a touch, got half-forward and defended it towards cover
on off and middle this time, decent pace, around 132 kmph, gets on the back foot and plays it back to Gul
and again, good length on the off and darting back in, pushed back to the bowler,bowling from a little wide of the crease and angling it in
easily done, Hopes has looked good here, not overpitched and he's not to the pitch either, swings in and he just punches it past the bowler, just a firm push, was beautifully timed
slower one, on the off stump, defends with a bit of a reach into the off side
down the leg side, twice he's done that, and this time he's punished with a wide
back of a length on the off, gets back and defends it firmly
kept a little low, landed on a good length outside off, Haddin lets it go
short of a good length on the off, gets back and punches it to cover, around 123 kmph
not the best of comebacks, at least looking at the way he's stared here, length ball on leg stump and Haddin works it away wristly between square leg and midwicket, four more
banged it in a little short on the off, blocked towards cover
swinging in a touch, brought it back in, struck him on the pads as he tried to turn it away, was missing leg
on middle and off, turns it towards midwicket
short of a good length on the off, defended towards midwicket off the back foot
coming back in from outside off, gets behind it and blocks, at 133.1 kmph
short on the off, gets back and pulls it over midwicket, hardly any intent there, managed to get it over the in-field for a couple, totally mistimed
slightly short, punches it wide of mid-off for a quick single
change of pace, bowled at 114.9 kmph, cut back in, defended into the leg side
fullish on leg stump, mistimes a drive to mid-on
just short on middle and off, defended to cover
back of a length outside off, chopped down to point

run out, Younis scores a direct hit from mid-off, ran to his left as it was pushed wide of him, Hopes set off for a single, stretched while trying to make it back in and replays indicate he was just short, the bails were dislodged when his bat was just short of the edge of the crease, the third umpire took his time and hit the red button
decide against the single this time, went in the same direction this time, wide of Younis but they won't make the same mistake again
on middle and leg, driven firmly back past the bowler just wide of mid-on but a diving stop prevents a single, Tanvir hits back with a maiden
fullish on the off stump, gets forward and bunts it to cover
dragged it on, good length on the off, was half-forward, hardly any element of conviction from the batsman, looked to block hard, got the inside edge and the stumps were rattled
full and wide, his pace has picked up, probably his fastest ball so far, 135.6 kmph, a hint of inward movement but wide enough for him to leave it alone
full on the off stump, dug out towards cover off the front foot
kept a little low but he dealt with it well, moving front and across and defending it to cover
pushed at it hard, wasn't quite to the pitch, got a thick outside edge towards third man, he's off the mark now
probing him outside off, pushed towards cover
beats the gap, a touch fuller and he's onto it, punches it wide of mid-off for three runs, nicely timed
played away from his body there, back of a length outside off, pushed towards point
shortish on middle, gets back and drops it short of square leg
short again on the off stump, blocks it short of cover on the back foot
on the stumps this time, bowled at 124 kmph, defended wide of Tanvir
bowled on a length on the off, opens the face to squeeze it wide of cover for a couple more
bowled from wide of the crease, settling into a nice rhythm here, maintained a decent pace even in these trying conditions, hitting 135.3 kmph, defended off the front foot
angling it on the pads, much quicker, almost 140 kmph, Clarke missed out there, should have tickled it fine but didn't get his bat onto it, manages a leg bye
poor ball, two in a row and Haddin is not so forgiving, full toss on leg stump, whips it away fine to beat short fine, a gift and all he can do his put his hands over his head
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot
attempted yorker, swinging in, ended up being a low full toss on leg stump, Haddin missed out this time, tried to flick it past square leg, got a faint inside edge onto his pads
banged it in short, on middle, defended back to the bowler
short of a good length on the off, gets across and defends it to cover
bowled at 132.5 kmph, pushes him back again, defended back to the bowler
much fuller, bowled on a length outside off and gets a hint of away movement, pushed to cover
good start, wide of the crease, on middle and off, defended towards mid-on
starts off with a maiden, short of a good length on the off, hitting the bat hard as he drops it short of point
good length on the off stump, reaches forward and pushes it to mid-off
pushing it  a touch fuller on the off, same result, defended to mid-off
angling it away from the right hander, gets across to dent the movement and plays it to cover
held its line this time, short of a length outside off, punched towards point
quick single puts pressure on Gul as he runs in from mid-on, just dropped short of him and Clarke set off, Gul ran over it and conceded another run
overthrows this time, sloppy stuff, fielded nicely with a stylish slide to his right and embarassed himself with a needless throw at the non-striker's end to throw away another run
fullish on the off, stroked firmly to mid-off
Clarke is handling this well, tight line, he moves front and across and defends it solidly wide of the bowler
firmly struck but straight to point, slightly short outside off, cut away but doesn't find the gap
stands tall and drives on the up, but back to the bowler, can Arafat pull off his second consecutive maiden?
nope, oversteps and almost had him lbw, offcutter, slower that Clarke failed to pick, moved well across to work it away, was struck in line and would have hit leg, too bad though

went after it, was standing well outside leg and the bowler chased him, tried to get it into the blockhole, Clarke reached forward and managed to squeeze it wide of mid-on, didn't time it well but had enough on it to take it to the boundary
shortish on middle, jumps up and he pushes it uppishly wide of a diving midwicket for a single
bringing it back in, fullish on the off, pushed back to the bowler
not much pace, but has been accurate in this second spell, tight line on the off stump, tries to play it to point, gets a thick inside edge back to the bowler
classy, too straight this time, in the zone for Clarke, who gets a stride across and whips it away between midwicket and mid-on, using his wrists, 50 up
he's spoiling it for Tanvir here, just a fraction overpitched on the off stump, his eyes light up and he drills it along the ground past the bowler for another four
too wide of the crease and darting it in, defended on the leg side
short of a good length on the off, punched wide of mid-off
misfield, what are the Pakistanis doing? Driven on the up wide of mid-off where Younis gifts a couple, letting it through is legs
some late movement there, length on the off and moved away, but he opened the face to play it to cover
short on middle and leg, tickled to square leg
full on the off, presents the full face to play it to mid-off, went off the middle
finally, just marginally wide and he guides it wide of point, and third man, for two runs
back of a length on middle, punched to mid-on off the back foot, quick single taken
tossed up on the off, pushed through the line to mid-off
slightly short on middle, punched off the back foot towards the bowler
on middle and off, gets forward and blocks on the off side
much fuller, giving it air, defends with a lunge
flighted on middle, pushed down the ground to long-on
short of a length on the off stump, gets back and drops it short of cover, quiet start against the spinner
another misfield, atrocious stuff, Shehzad at midwicket lets it through this time, one more run conceded
back of a length on middle and off, defended to cover
excellent timing, back of a length, gets front and across and bunts it back past the bowler, played with a straight bat to beat both mid-on and mid-off, Pup's looking good
offcutter, bowled at 119.7 kmph, pushed back to the bowler
straying in line now, pushed it wide of leg stump, given a wide, Pakistan have a looked sloppy after that double-strike
back of a length on the off, defended back to the bowler
short of a good length on middle, gets across and pushes it to midwicket
dipping into the right hander, closes the face and plays it back to the bowler
on middle, gets forward and turns it into the leg side
flighted on middle, gets across and pushes it wide of midwicket, Afridi has kept things quiet in his short spell so far
full on middle, waits for it and brings his bat down to block that into the leg side
on middle and off, spun away, pushed it wide of Afridi who dives to his left to save another single
good bowling, pushes in a googly, short on the off and spins in, defended off the back foot
flighted on the off, pushed down the ground to long-off
outside off, gets across the line to work it wide of the bowler, is hit on the pads
gets forward and plays it to midwicket
shortish on the off, reaches forward and drops it into the leg side
tossed up on the off, driven down the ground to long-on
comes down the track and bunts that to long-on to keep the strike. tidy start from Malik
tossed up on the off stump, takes it on the full and drives it wide of long-off, thinks of a second but it's not there
short on the off and spinning away, struck straight to cover
short on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
flighted on the off, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot
on the off stump, blocked towards cover, comes half-forward
a googly tossed up on the off from wide of the crease, gets a thick inside edge wide of square leg as he tries to play forward, Afridi has been impressive

bowled'im! A conventional offpsinner, landed on the off and spun in, Haddin moves well across to turn it into the leg side, missed and the ball clipped the leg stump, exposed his stumps there and paid the price
good length outside off, gets forward and drops it on the pitch
slightly short, gets to the pitch and dabs it into the off side
on the off stump, similar ball, identical result

appeal for lbw, short of a length outside off and spun back in to strike him on the pads as he tried to work it away, moved a little across, and replays indicate he may have just been struck in line, marginal call that
flighted on the off, pushed off the front foot to cover
short and wide, errs in length and pays, cuts it away behind point for a welcome boundary
drifting into the pads, comes down the track and kicks it away
appeal for lbw, the straighter one, drifting in towards middle, reaches forward and is struck on the pads, but just outside the line
important runs these, fraction short and he's onto it in a flash, steps away and slashes it wide of point for another four, two mistakes in this over and both have been dealt with
on the off stump, gets forward and taps it into the off side
gets down to sweep, spins in to hit him on the pads, outside the line again
shortish on the off, pushed through straight to cover off the back foot
gets outside the line and is struck on the pads again, he's been kept on a leash so far
tossed up, driven back to the bowler, the pressure builds
short on middle, played back to the bowler, finishes off with a maiden, excellent bowling
spun away, pitched outside leg and moved in towards middle, padded it awkwardly
fell just short, full on middle, pushed back uppishly but just in front of a diving Afridi
on middle and off, held it back, comes down the track and defends
missed out there, short on the off, attempted googly gone bad, rocked back to pull it away over midwicket, was a little too early into the shot, got an inside edge onto his pads
quicker one on the off stump, defended to cover
short outside off, moves away and bunts it to deep cover
tossed up on middle and leg, tickled to short fine
pushed off the front foot to cover, thinks of a single but Younis is onto it quickly
short on the off, gets back and defends it on the pitch
down the track, closes the face and turns it to midwicket
quicker one on middle and leg, spun back in sharply, worked away wide of short fine for a single
Symonds gets off the mark off his 12th ball, gets across and works it away wide of midwicket for a quick single, he'll be relieved now
tossed up outside off, paddles it well wide of square leg, wide of fine leg for a couple
shortish on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
gets back and pushes it to midwicket, slightly short on middle
flighted on the off, reaches forward and drops it short of cover
just a fraction short and he latches onto it, gets back and pulls it away to beat the gap between deep midwicket and deep square leg

trapped in front, held its line, landed on a good length on middle, was half-forward while playing at it, was expecting it to turn away but was beaten by the straighter one to be struck in line, big blow that, the spinners have done it again
on middle and off, gets on the back foot and defends into the leg side
flighted on the off, comes down the track and drives it back to the bowler
pushed off the front foot to cover
flighted on the off, turned away wide of square leg for a single
short on the off, gets back and punches it down the ground to long-on
short of a length outside off, tapped to cover off the back foot, another quiet over
flighted on middle and off, defended with a lunge
tossed up on the off, driven off the front foot to cover
held it back, dropped it sightly short, defended on the pitch
too full there, flighted, inviting him into the drive, Ferguson obliges, gets the pitch and creamed it between cover and mid-off, sweetly struck
googly, covers it well, gets outside the line and plays it wide of square leg
the straighter one on middle, gets outside the line and defends into the leg side
under pressure, short outside off, got back and punched it firmly through the covers, brings up the 100 for Australia
short on the off, gets back and pushes it to midwicket
short and wide, not got his length right here, struck away to deep cover
on the off stump, maintaining a shortish length, turns it wide of midwicket for a quick single
much fuller, outside off, gets across and is hit on the pads as he tries to turn it away
pushes him on the back foot, all six balls the conventional offspinners, hasn't bowled his doosra yet, defended to cover
tossed up outside off, tempted him into trying the slog-sweep, Clarke misses
tossed up, converts it into a full toss and drives it to long-on
tossed up on the off, spinning in, defended back to the bowler
held it back, dropped it short, pushed back past Malik to long-on
on middle and off, got back and defended it to midwicket
gave it some air again, gets outside off and drops it short of midwicket
tossed up outside off, pushed to midwicket
short on the off, not much conviction there, played it back to the bowler, they're struggling to even get the singles here
slightly short, punched down the ground to long-off
turned away off the back foot to square leg
oooh, pushed through quick and almost trapped him in front, gets back to defend and is rapped on the pads, but the faint inside edge saves him, spun in sharply
counters the spin well this time by getting to the pitch and sweeping it to deep midwicket
gets his foot across the line to paddle it towards deep square leg
short on the off, reaches forward to defend it into the off side
shortish on middle, pushed away to midwicket off the back foot
fails to beat the gap again, whips it to square leg, struggled to beat the in-field here
resorts to the paddle again, played wide of square leg this time for a single to keep the strike
tossed up on the off, spins in and he blocks it
short outside off, spins back in again, defended off the back
flighted outside off, defended once again, there are enough gaps but they just aren't looking for runs here
pushed away off the back foot into the leg side
tossed up outside off, finally the paddle, they get a couple wide of deep square leg
gets on the back foot and punches it to long-off, three off the over
plants his foot forward to defend, the grind continues
driven down the ground to long on
tossed up outside off, opens the face to guide it to point
pushed away off the back foot to midwicket, another dot ball
fetches it from outside off and paddles it down to fine leg, just a single
firmly struck, short on the off, struck down to deep midwicket, still not enough
sticking to regular offspin here, worked off the back foot to square leg
tickled down to fine leg for a single, Pakistan won't mind this at all
flighted on the off, gets across and just taps it to midwicket
takes a couple of steps forward and drives it down the ground to long-off
on and outside off again, turned to midwicket

failed to pick the straighter one there, tossed up, brought him forward and he played inside the line expecting it to spin in and drove at it, missed it in the end but retained his balance to ensure he didn't step out of the crease
on middle and leg, down the track and pushed to long-on
flighted on the off, gets in front and drives it straight to midwicket
struck away to square leg off the back foot
short and wide, gets back and chops it down to short third
gets well outside the line to paddle and is almost bowled as it zips in to just evade the leg stump
tossed up on middle and leg, paddled to fine leg for a single
short on middle and off, whipped away behind square
back of a length, punched to cover off the back foot
dropped it short, made room and cut it away behind point for a couple
shortish on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler off the back foot
gets to his fifty by tickling it fine for a couple, the message appears clear now, they've looked to get going this over
flighted outside off, gets across to paddle, is hit on the pads
on middle and leg, pushed away wide of midwicket
takes a couple of steps and turns it down to fine leg, oversteps, so freehit time
straighter one bowled quick and short outside off, swatted down to long-off, came onto him a little too quickly there, had shaped himself up for a pull
slower one this time, pushed short, tries to cut, is a little too early into it, misses
tossed up on middle, swept down to fine leg for a single
flighted on middle, charges down the track and drives it back to Malik
slightly short outside off, makes room and chops it wide of point for a single
short on the off stump, makes room and crashes it through the covers for a much-needed boundary
chased him as he stepped away, dropped short of cover for a quick single
shortish on the off stump, whipped away towards deep square leg for a single
quicker through the air, bowled at 93.4 kmph, comes down and pushes it to midwicket
full on middle, turned away to deep square leg for a single
the doosra, finally, spun away to catch him on the back leg as he tried to defend off the back foot, playing inside the line, but would have probably missed off
tossed up, pitches outside leg and spins in to strike him on the pads as he tries to close the face
short on leg stump, poor ball, rocks back and pulls it away over square leg, brings up the 50 partnership
short on middle, made room to cut that away, mistimed it to point, is disappointed with himself there
googly, quicker one, short on middle, played it wide of midwicket for a single
Ferguson plays his trademark shot, gets across to paddle it to fine leg

caught and bowled, stopped on him a little, dropped it short, spun away, stepped out of the crease and pushed at it, lobbed it straight to Afridi who took a dolly, went through with the shot there, didn't try to adjust to the spin, and paid the price
the paddle works for him, spun in, he dragged it from outside off to play it well wide of fine leg for a boundary
gets across the line and tickles it to short fine
flighted outside off, works it away to deep square leg to give the new man the strike
tossed up outside off, reaches forward and plays it back to the bowler
short on the off stump, gets back and punches it to midwicket
good stuff, dragged it short, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler, three consecutive dot balls in a powerplay
tossed up on the off stump, pushes it to cover off the front foot
slightly quicker on the off, opens the face and plays it to point
six consecutive dot balls, short on the off, fails to pierce the gap, plays it straight to point
tossed up outside off, was already into the paddle sweep before the ball was delivered, clipped his pads on the way to short third
what an over, short outside off, punched straight to cover, is this a maiden now?
googly, waited for it, hung his bat out, got the inside edge onto his pads, brilliant stuff from Afridi, Australia just haven't had any clue
good length on middle, driven down the ground to long-on
slower one, bowled at 114.2 kmph, cut back in, got back and pushed it to long-on
straying on the pads, see, they are able to negotiate these guys much better, flicked away to deep square leg
offcutter, gets away with a wide there, down the leg side, should have been given, or maybe not, replays show it went over leg stump
slower one, the third in a row, at 114 kmph, pulled away to deep square leg
definitely a wide this time, full outside leg stump, given
back of a length on middle, defended back to the bowler, five of the over, Australia will not be too happy
kept low, spun away, he prepared himself for a cut, didn't connect
spun away sharply to beat the outside edge, landed on middle and zipped away as he got back to defend, well done
flighted on middle, bunts it down the ground to long-on
drifting into the batsman, was the googly, got back and dropped it towards midwicket
googly again, kept low, short on the off, spun back in, got an inside edge onto his pads
bowled from wide of the crease, tickled it behind square leg, just two off the over
struck firmly but straight to cover, full on the off stump, fails to pierce the field
short of a length on middle, drops it wide of the bowler and sets off for a single
banged it short,saw him make some room, evaded it in the end, another dot ball
slower one bowled on a good length on the off, pushed to cover off the back foot, the struggle continues, Arafat has bowled ten deliveries not giving away too much
slower offcutter, pushed towards long-on for a single
back of a length on leg stump, punched towards long-on again,
slower one on the off, chops it short of point, mistimed a cut there
bouncer down the leg side, called a wide, will they even reach 200 here?
finally, a fraction overpitched, he moved away and creamed it through the covers, went off the middle, four valuable runs
two more, full on the off, made room to drive it into the gap between long-off and deep cover

was in the slot, struck it well, had a nice swing at it but there was fielder there perfectly positioned for that shot, hit towards long-on where Tanvir just had to take a couple of steps back to snap that one
good pace, good length on the off at around 135 kmph, played back to the bowler
slower one, an offcutter, makes room, opens the face to guide it wide of point for a couple
tossed up outside off, gets across and defends it short of midwicket
flighted on the off, pushes it back to the bowler off the front foot
tossed up on middle, turned away behind square leg
gave it some air, threw it up on the off stump, moved across and defended it to cover
slightly short on the off, got back and punched it down the ground
shortish on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler again
fullish on the off stump, drives it down the ground to long-on
low full toss on middle, pushed to long-on again
beats the outside edge with a legcutter this time, landed on a good length outside off and moved away as he tried to tap that off the back foot
slower one on the off, got onto the back foot, dropped it wide of the bowler, and set off
slower one on leg stump, pushed it back, they haven't gone after them at all
full outside off, reached for it, dragged it back past the bowler down to long-on for a single
tossed up outside off, worked it away behind square for a single
struck on the jaw, short outside off, slapped it back him, fell just short, brushed his fingers and struck him straight on the face
flighted on the off, comes down the track and drives it down to long-on, Shehzad fumbles and allows them to come back for the second
short on the off, swatted down the ground
Hauritz clears the boundary, the first six of the innings, tossed up on the off, bends down and slog-sweeps it over deep midwicket for a big one, came out of nowehere the way these two were going
drives it wide of cover off the front foot, a single again
inswinging yorker on the off, dug out back to the bowler, brushed Gul's fingers and crashed into the stumps at the non-striker's end
fullish but close to the off stump, pushed down to long-off for a single

gone! Slower one, bowled short on the off, an offcutter that, Hussey failed to pick it, struggled all the way through, tried to pull it over deep square leg, got the top edge as he was a little early into the shot, easy catch to Arafat
offcutter, turned away behind square for a single
beaten, short of a good length outside off, zipped away to beat the outside edge as he poked at it
played it wide of the bowler for a single towards mid-on
full outside off, swings it down to deep midwicket for a single
short on middle,. dropped wide of midwicket, some lethargic fielding by Shehzad there, took a while to cut it down and the batsmen are back for the second
short of a length on the off, swatted down to long-on, just a single
bouncer banged in too short, was too high as he went for the hook

poor keeping there, slower one, an offcutter on middle and it moved back in to beat the swing of the bat, Akmal failed to get behind it well, fumbled it to concede byes as Gul chased it down and dragged it back
dragged from outside off towards deep square leg for a single

inn2.comm: runs straightaway, poor start, down the leg side, Butt missed the attempt clip off his pads, and Haddin failed to get behind it, five runs first up
short of a good length outside off and came back in, left alone to the keeper, bowled at 122.3 kmph
beaten, testing him outside off, moved away just a touch to beat the outside edge
and again, just poking at it, fuller, a little wide outside off, reached for it but it moved away to beat the edge

came down the track, was bowled much straighter, pushed it wide of midwicket for a couple, a bit if hesitation out there on the middle as there is a fumble from Clarke while running back but all's well
teasing him outside off, moved away but he let it go this time
good length on the off, moves across and defends it back to the bowler
back of a length on the off, Shehzad was nicely behind it, tapped it wide of midwicket for a single
down the leg side, given, tries to glance it fine, he didn't really have to, got a free run
gets it outside off, moving away from the left hander, Butt has looked uncertain, pushed at it and pretended to withdraw once he was beaten
on middle and off, moving away, pushes it uppishly towards cover
short of a good length on leg stump, turned to square leg
firmly struck, got forward, presented the full face and squeezed it wide of mid-off but Hauritz id well diving to his right
juicy delivery on middle and leg, length ball, flicked away with ease wide of square leg, Pakistan are away
full outside off, chased it, tried to drive it through cover, the ball moved away to take the outside edge, well wide of second slip for a boundary
good length outside off, left alone to the keeper, held its line
good length on the off, moving back in, defended to cover
held it back, bowled at 125 kmph, came back in a touch, stood tall and defended it to cover
nipped back in again, he had left his crease, tried to dab it into the off side, got an inside edge onto his pads
jumped off the pitch, driving length, Butt left it alone and Haddin took it over his head
good length outside off, decent pace, around 136.4 kmph, swung away, left alone
came back in, short on the off, got back and defended it back to the bowler
nicely done, fraction short on the off, whipped it away to fine leg
zipped away, beaten all ends up, bowled at 135.9 kmph, landed on a good length on middle and moved away late to beat the outside as he moved back to defend
slightly short on the off, taps it towards cover
shortish on leg stump, takes his bottom hand off to drop it on the leg side
beaten, Bracken has bowled well, not for the first time is he beating the outside edge, got it to shape away from the right hander as  Shehzad came half-forward to defend
a touch too straight, into his zone, worked away wide of midwicket to give his senior partner the strike
fraction short, moves across and cuts it away wide of point, third man cuts it off but the throw is slightly wayward, Butt was struggling a bit while coming back for the second
slightly short on middle, hit on the ribs as he tries to turn that away
held its line this time, landed short outside off and moved away, left it alone
testing him outside off, gets across and dabs it to cover
short on the off, defended short of cover
angling it into the pads, tickled to fine leg
good length on middle and leg, defended, walking forward to play it to mid-on
short on leg stump, turned to midwicket, in no hurry here
bouncer on middle, at 139.4 kmph, Butt ducks under it well
zipped past the outside edge, the late movement almost did him in again, fishing for it with very little foot movement, playing away from his body and is lucky to be there
much closer to the off stump, still wide enough for him to let it go, came back in just a touch
angling it away, runs it down to third man for a single
charges down the track and creams it over cover, was in the slot, made some room and got  a free flow of the arms
back of a length on middle, defended off the back foot into the leg side
bent low, rolled his wrists over it, struck it between point and cover, just a fraction short, seized the length early and dispatched it to the boundary
slower one, cut back in, countered it well by closing the face to play it to midwicket
bowling to his strength, on middle and leg, worked away firmly wide of midwicket for three runs, Hauritz gives chase, the runs are coming freely
slightly short outside off, held its line, left it alone
punched firmly towards Clarke at point where a slight fumble allows them a single
good length on the off, gets to the pitch and pushes it to cover
cut back in, bowled at 130 kmph, defended solidly to cover
good length outside off and moving away, left alone to the keeper
slightly short on the off, punched to cover off the back foot
jumped off the pitch, hit the track hard, tried to upper-cut that, missed
angling it into the pads, tries to whip it away, struck on the thighs
on middle and leg, gets across and works it away to fine leg
short of a good length on the off, tapped towards cover
came back in this time, identical result, played from the crease
good length outside off, tries to drive it through the line, gets a thick outside edge to third man, not quite an offside player this guy
darting back in, defended to cover off the back foot
short of a length, cut away, but straight to point
back of a length on middle, punched back to the bowler
leaving the left hander, Butt pushes at it, he doesn't move his feet much, gets a thick edge to third man
back of a length on middle, dropped into the off side
slightly short on the off, punched to cover off the back foot
went after it, tried to clear the in-field on the off side, struck it on the up just wide of mid-off, got no elevation there but a single still
short of a good length on the off, dabbed down to third man
bouncer banged in short on middle and leg, Shehzad ducks under it easily
banged in short on middle, pulled away to deep midwicket, kept it down
poor ball, straying on the pads, Butt tickles it fine to beat the fielder in the deep, four more
good length on the off, reaches forward to defend it to cover
slightly short outside off, a legcutter that one, left it alone, a touch too harsh there as he calls it a wide, was within his reach
charged out and dismissed it over midwicket, swung across the line there but timed it well, cleared the in-field comfortably, a couple of bounces before getting to the ropes, 50 up
back of a length on the off, defended to cover
saw him come down and banged it short, Shehzad adjusted well to back away from it
four more, slower one banged in short, around 107 kmph, pulled it away over midwicket, didn't time it all too well, but well enough to carry it to the ropes, safe shot, he's opening up
nipped it back in this time, walked forward and defended it solidly
round the wicket to the left hander, flighted on middle, dug out back to the bowler
threw it up, got it to spin away, reached forward to defend, the spin caused an outside edge and they get a single wide of point
gets across and works it away to square leg
flighted on the off, pushed to midwicket
and again, on middle and off, driven straight to him again
angling it in, clipped towards fine leg to keep the strike
just a fraction full, gives him the charge and tries to swipe that past mid-on, mistimes it, gets a single, but good positive signs here from the youngster
offcutter, whipped away to midwicket from the crease
good length on middle and leg, moves across and defends it back to the bowler
beats a diving point, pushed away from the body, but there's cover in the deep
short of a good length outside off, run down to third man, he's looking pretty fluent now
short outside off, slashed away really hard to third man, keeps the strike
fraction short outside off, chopped down to point
drifting into the left hander, defended to cover, held its line
tossed up on middle, comes down and works it away to midwicket
tossed up on middle, lunges forward to defend into the leg side
slightly short on leg stump, gets back and punches it to mid-on, holding its line again
a maiden, pushed through straight on the off, gets forward and taps it towards cover
good length on the off, pushed to cover off the back foot
short on the off stump, comes down the track and strikes it straight to midwicket, didn't time it well
banged in short outside off, run down to third man
was bogged down for a bit, but seized on the opportunity when it was on offer, a fraction wide, came down the track and smashed it over mid-off for a boundary
back of a length on the off, chopped down to point, bent low and dabbed it down
nicely done, walked across to a fullish delivery on leg stump, tickled it wide of fine leg for a couple more
bowled flatter on the off stump, defended towards cover
on middle and off, tries to work it behind square, is hit high on the pads
short on the off stump, punched to midwicket
flighted on middle, gets forward and works it to square leg
straighter one, flighted outside off, got forward, played inside the line, got a thick edge and hit Haddin's pads, too thick an edge to be called a dropped chance that
on middle and off, pushed off the front foot to midwicket
slightly short outside off, chopped down to cover
struck firmly, slightly short outside off, moves back and smacks it into the gap between long-off and deep cover
similar delivery but much straighter, on middle, punched to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, spinning away, left alone
too wide, short, all the ingredients for a perfect cut shot, that's exactly what Butt does, waits for it and slashes it away wide of a diving point
pushed firmly off the front foot towards deep cover where there's a fumble, and they get back fotr the second, the pressure's building on Australia with every run
tossed up on the off stump, comes down the track and chips it wide of long-on for a single, Hilfenhaus fields well running to his left
angling it into the pads, tries to work it away, gets a legbye wide of midwicket
gets across the line to turn it away, struck on the pads outside the line
flighted on the off, reaches forward and pushes it to point
flat, and pushed through quick, wasn't there to cut but Shehzad had his eyes on the gap in the off side, made room, got his bat down in time and cut it between cover and point for a boundary
bowled full on middle, down the track and pushes it back to the bowler
flighted outside leg, swept down to fine leg for a single
flighted on middle, comes down the track and drives it down to long-on
tossed up on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler
slightly short on the off, dabbed down to cover
on middle and leg, moves across and turns it to square leg
flighted outside off, gets to the pitch and drives it straight to midwicket
flighted on the off, driven straight to cover
spun away after landing on a good length on the off, reached forward but was almost done in by the bounce
short on the off, punched to cover
beaten again, shot up and away from outside off to beat the outside edge as he tried to play that off the back foot
tossed up outside off, driven between point and cover for a single
tossed up on the off, charges down and chips it over mid-off for a boundary, the runs keep coming, and these two are inching towards a century stand
short and wide, cut away to deep cover
short on the off, worked away uppishly towards midwicket
tossed up on the off, reaches forward and defends
on middle and leg, gets on the back foot and works it away to square leg
flighted on the off, driven towards midwicket
slightly short on the off, gets back and drops it dead on the pitch

edged and gone! He had troubled Butt, and eventually got rid of him. Tossed up, drifting into the left hander and spun away after landing on a good length, Butt tried to open the face, got an edge and Clarke took a dolly at slip

Hauritz strikes again! Stopped on him and bounced more than he expected, hit the high end of the bat as he tried to play that off the back foot, lobbed up towards midwicket where Symonds took a good catch diving forward
survives, slightly short on middle, gets back and punches it to mid-on
tossed up outside off, opens the face to play it wide of point
short outside of, pushed off the back foot wide of cover
pushed him back with a quicker one on the off, dropped wide of the stumps, excellent over that, but he's only got four more to go after this
flighted outside off, turned away to square leg
flighted on the off, pushed wide of point for a quick single
Misbah goes after it, came out of nowhere after that sleep-inducing innings in the first ODI, flighted on middle and he lofted it cleanly over long-on, less than a hundred needed now
on middle and leg, pushed into the leg side
played straight to midwicket
tucked away behind square for a single to keep the strike
on middle and leg, bowled with a flat trajectory, turned away between midwicket and square leg for a single
down the leg side, tries to clip it away, Haddin takes off the bails, his foot was in the air for a bit but brought it back down in time by the time he took off the bails
quicker one bowled short on the off, pushed back to the bowler
flighted on the off, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
short of a good length on the off, pushed to midwicket off the back foot
spun in to beat the outside edge as he tried to cut that off the back foot
reached forward to guide it wide of short third, there's a fumble and they grab a single
wicket off his first ball, needless shot, tossed up outside off, tried to clear the long-on boundary, mistimed it and Hauritz just had to run back a few steps to pouch an easy one

arm ball does the trick! He failed to pick it, flat and quick on the off, dipping in, was pushed back and tried to whip it through the leg side, failed to get his bat down in time and the stumps took a beating!
survives, tossed up on the off, defended solidly to cover
turns it away wide of square leg for a single, big cheers
flighted on the off, driven through cover for a single
tossed up outside off, got outside the line and paddled it fine for a couple, Clarke was appealing but that clearly came off the bat

appeal for stumping, beat the outside edge, played inside the line and was done in by the straighter one, his foot is just behind the line as he lunged forward, Haddin clipped off the bails and was confident that was out, but replays indicate he was just in
appeal for lbw, rapped on the pads, spun back in sharply to catch him  just outside the line, Pakistan are struggling
short on middle, defended into the leg side off the back foot
tossed up on the off, pushed back to the bowler
poor ball, tossed up, dragged it too short, got back and punched it through the point region, a pressure-relieving boundary that
flatter on middle, pushed off the back foot to midwicket, end of an eventful over
tossed up outside off, paddled towards deep square leg for a single
dipping into the right hander, defended solidly to cover
short and wide, cut uppishly towards point
dropped into the vacant leg-side field and they set off for a single
arm ball again but on leg stump, pushed to a slightly deepish mid-on for a single
flighted on the off, eased through to deep cover for a single
two more, quicker one on middle and leg, tickled wide of fine leg for a couple
on middle and off, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
flighted on the off, defended back to the bowler
threw it up, Afridi playing sensibly now, swept down to fine leg
quicker one bowled flat outside off, reaches forward and pushes it to cover
on middle and leg, pushed away to midwicket

and another one goes! Oh this is some suicidal batting, I tell you! Clarke proposes, Afridi accepts with a wild two-step and a slash of the bat only to give Hussey a juggling catch at first slip, the wheels are coming off Pakistan's gravy train
slower ball, tossed up on middle and off, watchfully defended
flights it on a lovely length and Akmal plays it back again
and more of the conservative stuff from Akmal
sees some width and drives hard but cannot beat cover
tosses it up invitingly outside off stump, starts to dip, Akmal hesitates and then goes for a fiesty square-drive, bottom-edging it into the turf
flatter trajectory, a touch short, Malik punches off the back foot
quicker, flatter, and steered off the back foot to backward point
slower and fuller, driven back off the front foot to Hauritz
tidy line again, just pitching on a length, and he defends
tosses it up to commit him onto the front foot, defending it back
spins in from wide and he opens the face, steering it to the fielder
tossed up outside off, defended towards cover
poor cricket all around, juicy waist high full that should have been punished but wasn't, Malik missed it completely, and so did Haddin and it rolled down for four byes
on middle and  off, defended into the off side
flighted on the off, driven straight to cover
slightly short on middle and turned away sharply, defended it a little awkwardly off the back foot
on middle and off, pushed towards cover again, the match has turned on its head here
driven neatly wide of cover, there's a deep cover in place but two more
poor ball, short outside off, punched away wide of deep cover for a couple more
quicker one on the off, reached forward and placed it wide of point for a single
flatter on the off, moved across and pushed it back to Symonds
slightly short outside off, tapped towards point off the back foot
flighted on the off, pushed through to midwicket
nicely done, on middle and off, eased through the covers for a single
they're taking singles fairly easily now, quicker one bowled flat and full, driven to deep cover
on middle and off, pushed off the front foot to cover
much straighter on middle, paddled wide of square leg for a single
on middle and leg, tickled wide of square leg for a single
drifting into middle and leg, reaches forward and blocks
on middle and off, dropped short of point
tossed up on middle, driven down the ground to long-on
short on middle, turned wide of square leg for a single
pushed him back with a quicker one, punched to midwicket
flighted outside off, drilled through to deep cover, all along the ground
trips as Symonds slams into him, Malik fell flat on the ground and Akmal was deprived of a single as he pushed it back past the bowler, and Symonds dived full length to his right to stop it
swinging it into the right hander from round the wicket, pushed through to mid-off
slower one, full on the pads, clips it away stylishly to deep square leg
poor running, pushed towards long-off, and Akmal called for a single but Malik sent him back thinking the fielder was up, it went to long-off and they didn't get a run, atrocious
angling into the right hander, cut away to beat the outside edge as he came forward to defend
the slower one does him in, landed full on middle and leg and he just chipped it to Hopes at mid-on, bowled at 109 kmph, he clearly didn't pick it and Australia are on top now
swinging into the right hander, pushed to mid-on, the pressure is all over Pakistan now
tossed up on the off, pushed towards cover off the front foot
slightly short on middle, turned away behind square for a single
tossed up on the off, lunges forward and pushes it towards cover
short on middle, whipped away towards deep square leg for a single
low full toss on the off, pushed straight to midwicket
zipped in to catch him on the thighs, spun in from outside of and Malik was clearly surprised by the turn
slower one, bowled at 113.3 kmph, defended towards cover
driving length, cut away as he chased it, beat the outside edge
full outside off, bowled at 114 kmph, opens the face and drives it to point
low full toss on the off stump, driven straight to mid-on

angling in to the right hander, pushed off the front foot to mid-off, calls for a single, is sent back
short of a length on the off, cut away wide of deep cover for a single

short on leg stump, rapped on the pads as he tries to turn it away

short on the off and spun away, handled it well, dropped it with soft hands short of cover
on middle and off, driven off the front foot to midwicket
short and wide, cuts it away to point, Clarke fields
good length on the off, defended towards cover
full outside off, opens the face to guide it wide of point towards third man

good length outside off, held its line, left alone to the keeper
shortish on the off, swatted back to the bowler
pushed off the front foot towards midwicket

Arafat swings and misses and the stumps are pegged back! The pressure was building, they failed to get the singles and he had a desperate swipe at a full ball outside off, missed it, it spun in to strike the off stump
angling it into the left hander, closes the face to work it wide of midwicket and get off the mark
flighted on the off, pushed off the front foot to midwicket
paddled away fine, dragged it from well outside off, fine leg is a little too square and he finds the gap, they need some more of those
good length on the off, bowled at 113.3 kmph, defended to point
offcutter, gets forward and guides it down to third man
short and wide, cuts it down to third man, the scoreboard's ticking again
angling it into the left hander, defended solidly towards cover

pushed through quick on the off stump, dropped short of the bowler
gets across the line and tries to work it into the leg side, is hit on the pads, appeal turned down
pushed of the front foot towards cover
excellent fielding, short outside off, tried to late-cut it, almost pulled it off, Clarke dived to his left at slip and prevented a certain four

in the blockhole outside off, dug out towards cover
good length on the off stump, plants his foot forward and dabs it to point

appeal for stumping, zipped away to beat the outside edge, he had reached forward to defend, Haddin collected and clipped the bails, Tanvir tried to drag it back but it appears his foot is bang on the line when the bails were dislodged, or maybe not, the third-umpire is taking his time and after several replays he seems to have decided that a part of his foot was just behind the line, fair call.
held its line, he defended outside the line with bat close to pad

appeal for a catch, tossed up outside off, got outside the line to sweep it square, lobbed up off the pads and Haddin appealed for a catch, Bowden refers with Rauf, and gives it not out. Correct decision, replays show there was no contact with the bat

appeal for lbw, flighted on the off, tried to sweep it fine, missed, was rapped on the pads and the first replay showed he was struck just in line with middle and leg, Bowden shook his head immediately, but was a really close call
on middle and off, pushed into the off side wide of the bowler, ends an eventful over
goes after it, good length outside off, chips it comfortably over mid-off for a couple, 32 needed off 29
beaten, pushed through quick, bowled at 131.5 kmph, poked at it but it went through too quickly
quick single, pushed through the line to mid-off and they scamper through
shuffled from one end to the other and worked it away to square leg for a single
short of a good length outside off, at 131 kmph, tries to run it down, misses
sent back, punched to cover but there's no chance of a single there, 30 needed off the last four now
length ball on the off stump, driven firmly down to long-on for a single
he's gone! Is that the decisive blow? Came onto him quick, short on middle, was tempted, went for the pull, got the top-edge and Hussey at midwicket ran to his left to complete an easy catch

run out, now that's definitely the decisive wicket, slower one outside off, tries to chop it down, gets an under-edge on the bounce to Haddin, Malik sets off for a single, is sent back, an under-arm flick from the keeper crashes into the stumps and the former Pakistan captain is well short
fullish on the off stump, pushed off the front foot to mid-on
hit by the bouncer, went off the shoulder onto the helmet as he tried to back away
wide down the leg side, tries to glance it down fine, misses

Bang on the stumps, has a wild swing, misses, and timber!!
